
 This is the 'ioko-tapestry-commons' project.

 This project includes a series of {{{http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html}GPL}} licensed components to aid building tapestry websites.

The Projects

 * {{{./tapestry-caching/}Tapestry Caching}} - Provides caching of the generated HTML for a page snippet

 * {{{./tapestry-swfObject/}Tapestry SWF Object}} - Provides a component that adds a SWF object to the page and includes 'swfobject' javascript library to add it. Includes an 'easy' way of binding flashvars.

 * {{{./tapestry-cacheControl/}Tapestry Cache Control}} - Provides a component that a HTTP headers to control page caching based on global settings and page specific annotations


Using the libraries

 The easiest way is to add them is by using maven (or other build systems) dependencies

+--
 <dependency>
    <groupId>uk.co.ioko</groupId>
    <artifactId>tapestry-caching<artifactId>
    <version>1.1.0</version>
 </dependency>
 <dependency>
    <groupId>uk.co.ioko</groupId>
    <artifactId>tapestry-swfObject<artifactId>
    <version>1.1.0</version>
 </dependency>
 <dependency>
    <groupId>uk.co.ioko</groupId>
    <artifactId>tapestry-cacheControl<artifactId>
    <version>1.1.0</version>
 </dependency>
+--

 If you haven't already added it you need to add the tapestry.formos.com maven repository to your POM.

+--
 <repositories>
        <!-- Chances are, this one is known because that's where this very POM comes from! -->
        <repository>
            <id>tapestry</id>
            <url>http://tapestry.formos.com/maven-repository</url>
        </repository>
 </repositories>
+--

